commit.message: added nvmlDeviceGetCudaComputeCapability function from nvml API
Updated readme
Updated version number

Added warning message to nvidia_smi xmldevicequery

I think this was only ever meant to be an example in the original nvml
library. Given that nvidia update the nvidia smi query, it will be too
hard to keep this query up to date. Instead, calling 'nvidia-smi -q -x'
from python with subprocess would achieve the same result.

Search locations for nvml.dll on windows

Adding a list of search paths for NVML.dll on Win10.

On my Win10, nvml was found in system32. It was installed by the nvidia official installer.

commit.message: Added docstrings to functions

Fix for more than 8 GPUs

Fix for an error in grab_gpus which failed when nvmlDeviceGetCount() > 8
Added new statuses and enums
Add link to readthedocs
Made python2 compatible
Changed warning code and return results
Added get_free_gpus function
Added get_free_gpus functionality in utils
Updated Readme
Updated README to include more info on py3smi
Updated py3smi to handle dead gpus
Added exception handling for regex fail
